metadata.name: Urban Inception Redux #93
metadata.description:
Urban Inception Redux borrows from the original Circle City project and goes bigger, 6x bigger to be exact, and adds a whole new alternate reality, more rings, and a new skew potential. 

PLEASE BE PATIENT - This project has a lot of computations and may take a minute or two to render. 

This project creates a 12 layer composition that can be exported as an SVG and plotted or used to cut a physical out of wood or acrylic using a laser. With each layer being a single contiguous element. 

More info about the project and physicals can be found at: 
https://alleditions.art/p/urban-inception-redux

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: abstraction #73
metadata.description:
Diagrams of patterns on spheres, planets, fields, and platonic solids rendered isometrically. Ink on paper (on js).

Press DOWN to save an SVG suitable for plotting (or laser etching).
Press UP to save a 2400 x 2400 png. If you need a bigger image, zoom out and refresh, the canvas will fit the window.

Physics is fundamentally idealist. We search for simple rules from which the complexities of the universe emerge. But real systems are exceptionally complex, closed-form solutions are the exception. The deeper we dive into the fundamental nature of the universe, the less clear the rules become. Are the rules we've developed fundamental, or are they empirical approximations?

metadata.name: Omega Point #50
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #24
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

metadata.name: Fronteras en abstracto #220
metadata.description:
A place in the abstract, walking in one direction without knowing if you will reach that place. Then, in case you find it, go to the other side before dawn.

It's just a game of words and phrases that have to be given meaning, and we find it on the frontier of something that we don't know what it is.

Un lugar en abstracto, caminando en una dirección sin saber si se llega a ese lugar. Luego, en caso de encontrarlo, pasar al otro lado antes del amanecer.

Es solo un juego de palabras y frases a las cuales hay que darles sentido, y lo encontramos en la frontera de algo que no sabemos qué es.

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #27
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Kinetics #494
metadata.description:
CONTROLS
 * Pause a Kinetic by clicking on the canvas.
 * Increase and decrease the p5js framerate by tapping the left and right arrows.
 * Pause the top layer by tapping down arrow.
 * Save a frame by tapping S.
 * Press H for High Quality, M for Default, L for Low Quality. Note, this effects performance.
 * Reset the Kinetic by by tapping backspace.

Kinetics is a neo-constructivist generative art project built using p5js. Each Kinetic delicately moves from it's origin, giving the appearance of infinite space and possibility. The viewer witnesses the construction of the Kinetic floating inside of the negative. Shapes and lines move around the Kinetic in a dazzling display of contrasting color.

The texture developed for Kinetics, deemed The Creation of the Universe (See top right) is at its core a color gradient of 3 different colors. Each piece construct's itself, drawing lines on top of lines to create a unique self contained assembly of materials as opposed to a realistic abstraction. The Creation of the Universe repeats itself in each piece, just as cells do in an organic structure. From here is where it initially got it's name.

Inspired heavily by the works of Rodchenko and Tatlin, each Kinetic appears to slot together like a puzzle. Each piece has multiple hard edge planes clashing aggressively with each other giving the sense that there is more than just a flat canvas. A quasi realism is created through our desire to build instead of simply paint.

"Long Live Generative Art"

- Mitchell

metadata.name: Resilience  #184
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022
